data.content:
Three things break in EF Core 10. Here's each one with the fix:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` — now takes a lambda, not an expression tree

Your entire expression tree construction code no longer compiles. Replace it with a simple lambda:

```csharp
// EF Core 10 — simple lambda with conditionals
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

---

### 2. Complex type column names — two changes generate rename migrations

**Sibling disambiguation:** `ShippingAddress.Street` and `BillingAddress.Street` now get uniquified names (e.g., `Street1`). **Nested path change:** `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` maps to `Payment_BillingAddress_City` instead of the old `BillingAddress_City`.

Both will generate column-rename migrations. To preserve existing column names, pin them explicitly:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b => {
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress, sb =>
        sb.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("ShippingAddress_Street"));
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress, sb =>
        sb.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_Street"));
});

// For nested complex types:
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>(b => {
    b.ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment, pb =>
        pb.ComplexProperty(p => p.BillingAddress, ab =>
            ab.Property(a => a.City).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City")));
});
```

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` — new `logCommandText` parameter

Every method on the interface now has an additional `string logCommandText` parameter. Add it:

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection, DbCommand command,
        DbContext context, Guid commandId, Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)          // ← new parameter (redacted SQL)
    { /* logging — use logCommandText for safe log output */ }
}
```

Update **all** methods on the interface (`CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.) the same way.
